    {
      "id": "text_step_0",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "The water cycle begins with evaporation, where the sun heats up bodies of water like lakes and oceans.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 200
    },
    {
      "id": "text_step_1",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "As the water gets warmer, it turns into vapor that rises into the air due to heat energy from the environment.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 200
    },
    {
      "id": "text_step_2",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "When this warm moisture reaches higher altitudes with cooler temperatures, condensation occurs forming clouds.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 200
    },
    {
      "id": "text_step_3",
      "type": "text",
      "description": "Eventually, when saturated enough, these water droplets combine and grow until they are heavy enough to fall as precipitation (rain or snow) back onto the Earth's surface.",
      "x": 150,
      "y": 200
    }
  ],
